          <msContents>
            <summary>
              <p>  </p>
              <p>216 fol.; Writing surface: parchment; Shelfmark: E. H. 5; Qurʾānic Text: complete Qurʾān codex; 20 lines per page; Dimensions: 305 x 308mm.</p>
              <p> </p>
              <p>This entry is based on the catalogue of Fehmi E. Karatay (1888-1968). Currently we do not have access to the images. With exceptions, the catalogue does not contain precise information on the distribution of the text throughout the pages. For this reason, only fol. 1 is given. </p>
              <p> </p>
              <p><ref target="https://www.zotero.org/groups/corpuscoranicum_pub/items/itemKey/UEN2FUP7" sameAs="UEN2FUP7" type="zotero">Karatay (1962) </ref>describes the manuscripts as follows, p. 21: "59 E. H. 5. Aynı. Parşömen. 308mm boy ve 305mm eninde 216 yaprak. Sahifede kûfi yazı ile 240mm uzunl.[uğunda] 20 satır. Tahminen III-IV, (IX-X) asırda istinsah edilmiştir. Sure İsimleri kırmızı ile yazılmıştır. Miklep ve yazma şemseli siyah deri Osmanlı cildi. Tam bir Kuran nüshasıdır."</p>
              <p> </p>
              <p>This can be translated as follows: "59 E. H. 5. Same. Parchment. 216 leaves of 308 mm height and 305 mm width. The text area [contains] 20 lines measuring 240 mm. Probably copied during the 3rd-4th (9th-12th) century. Sūra names are written in red. Black leather Ottoman binding with flap (miklep) and a mandorla (yazma şemse). The codex is a complete one/it is a complete Qurʾān codex."</p>
            </summary>
